cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network slicing and resource allocation in wireless networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses maximizing the sum rate of multiple mobile network operators. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a game theoretical framework for solving the slice allocation problem. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is relevant as the paper uses a many-to-one matching game framework to solve the slice allocation problem. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper investigates the role of power allocation in small cell base stations for maximizing data rate.
